Guess we'll find out in May after Jeremy Jahns and Chris Stuckman review it..  Btw, I'm not a Star Wars fanatic, but if you're going to have a film marketed as a "Star Wars Story" it might be wise to do more than just fill it with familiar props and hire a director who's an old friend of the creator to replace two weaker directors.   If they still plan on doing an Obi-Wan Kenobi stand-alone film, I really hope they don't go in this direction.. In fact, they should get the folks who wrote and directed Logan to do the Obi-Wan Kenobi stand-alone film.  IMHO   .....

I feel like every character referenced in theses side movies are somehow going to make it into the 9th movie; then it will really be Marvel infinity war. Star wars shouldnt look at what other movies are doing, modern movies are supposed to take from star wars. I didnt really have an opinion about episode 7 i thought it was alright - if not a new hope remake, but then I had to digest the disgrace that was episode 8. text: This looks like a fun movie - I'm gonna check it out for sure. In my opinion The Last Jedi was pretty great in a lot of ways, I personally loved that it challenged expectations. So far I'm really happy with what Lucasfilm have done and are doing given the crazy pressure they must be under (mostly from so-called fans, to deliver their individual and highly specific vision of what these films and characters should be, oh and those shareholder $$$). A lot of the comments here, and the hate on display, is surprising and not at all what I'd expect from the Star Wars community of fans. It's like the haters haven't actually learned anything from watching the Lucas era films and incorporated any of that into how they conduct themselves as human beings, how sad is that!? It just comes off as puerile entitlement... What I observe when I watch behind the scenes footage (especially after watching the director and the Jedi documentary) is many talented individuals who deeply love Star Wars and are giving their all to honour Lucas' legacy, but also establish a new trajectory. Of course if you really don't enjoy these films, that's perfectly fine. But it's too easy to just sit there and be so damned negative - I assume you are here because you are a Star Wars fan - which means you're better than that. Or you're a troll, in which case - meh, move along.

text: REALLY getting tired of Disney using their abandonment of the expanded universe to make a blatant and unnecessary changes. Apparently my pet peeve for this movie is the unnecessary need to change the Millenium Falcon, fight the fact that the YT 1300 had a pretty stock appearance. I get their money grabbing needs to change everything else, but they literally could have left that little detail alone and ran with it. It's like every one of these new movies that have come out have dangled something from the expanded universe in our faces and then shat on it, rub out faces in it, and then told us to swallow.  When Disney first bought out Star Wars I defended them because I enjoyed what they did with the Marvel Cinematic Universe. I had high hopes that they would finally get out of the Empire Era and start making movies about the Old Republic or even before. Or maybe we would finally get a movie purely from The Darkside perspective, for the forming of the Sith.  Now not only do I no longer expect it I'm not even sure if I'd want to see it.

text: Disney's Star Wars "side stories" are better than their main films because the characters are victims of probable, well-established circumstances and within these circumstances, they struggle to get through. Whereas the main films operate out of geocentricity‚ÄîCharacters are walking deus ex machinas without credible ingenuity or skill, of which the world and all its events revolve around.   Overpowered ‚â† Bad Storytelling.  Overpowered characters are completely justified if focus is first attributed to world-building and the Magic Rules that world adheres to. Once the rules are established, characters can "rampage" to their heart's desire just as long as they stay within the limitations of the established rules (These are some of the best stories).  The problem of the main films isn't any one specific character but the failure to accurately set up circumstances that are believable irrespective to the "A-team" as well as failure to at least hint at lore rules before a feat is performed.
author: Eriick Brown

Yeah it's expanding off of a character we already know and love, but at least it's a fresh take. They won't have to sit and reference the OT just to please fans. I think telling Solo's origin story is a great way to take the series to a new place while still having a tinge of familiarity to keep us grounded in the universe.

text: I actually cannot wait to see this movie, and I am as big a Star Wars fan as the rest of the people who hated the last few. The movies are never going to be the same as they were before, but that does not mean that the new ones can't offer us a new take on Star Wars and exciting stories that get your blood pumping. The fantastic thing about Star Wars is that the universe is so expansive that nearly anything is possible, and that means that there are nearly limitless stories to tell. Am I blind to the flaws in the newer movies? No, I am not. I just choose to focus on the positives instead of heading into a movie saying "This movie is going to be garbage" and "boycott this movie". The Last Jedi and The Force Awakens both had their flaws, but they also had a lot of features that I loved.

text: Well, from what I've seen, I already have a bad feeling about this.  First of all, I didn't really feel any sense of excitement or hype for the film through the trailers. Even Last Jedi, which everyone hated, did better with its trailers.  Second of all, I know I might be nitpicking, but I don't like the style of the title shown here. Seriously, it's like, large, chunky, spinning letters. It looks more kiddish than even the logo of Star Wars's kid-focused show, Star Wars Rebels. Even from the title, I'm worried about the style and mood they're going for.  Lastly, reviews have already come in, with scores placing in the low 70-60s. That's basically a C-F tier. So, yeah.  I'm only going to see it to (hopefully) gain a little bit more lore on the Pre-Battle of Yavin era, because, well, I'm kind of a Star Wars geek. Other than that, I don't expect to enjoy it.

text: Wait. So the "Star Wars Story Saga" is a prequel to the Original Star Wars Trilogy. But it's also a sequel to the Prequel Trilogy. But it's technically neither part of the Prequel Trilogy or the Original Trilogy. So in a sense, this is some sort of Mid-quel, if you will. But if you think about it, since the Original Trilogy is now sandwiched between the Prequel Trilogy and the Sequel Trilogy, then really that should be considered the "Mid-quels". That means The Prequel Trilogy is the prequel to the "Mid-quel" Trilogy. Likewise, the "Mid-quel" Trilogy is the sequel to the Prequel Trilogy. But now we have a problem. If the Original Trilogy is the "Mid-quel" Trilogy, then The Star Wars Story Saga cannot be the "Mid-quel" Trilogy anymore. So if the Star Wars Story Saga is not a "Mid-quel" Saga, but it is still a sequel to the Prequel Trilogy, then in my crazy Trilogy fantasizing, they must be something in between. I shall call these the Premidquels! Genius!

text: Hello this is Generation Z, aka the future.  I first saw the originals when I was six, then prequels, and have seen the last four Star Wars in theaters.  Let me just say that I thought that The Last Jedi was an amazing film on a lot of levels.  And for all of the fanboys that can't handle the fact that some people love different content, welcome to reality.  The Last Jedi went very different than a lot of people including Mark Hamill expected.  That's life.  Unexpected things happened and that's what made The Last Jedi so real.  In regards to Solo, all you whiners out there who boycotted it for the stupidest reasons ever, you just missed out on the best 2 hours and 15 minutes of your lives.  Thanks for perhaps ruining what could have been one of the greatest trilogies Star Wars could have gotten.  Solo was a masterpiece and I hope that people realize that because I need sequels!  Thank you Lucasfilm for your amazing work.  We're behind your efforts! All you fanboys who can't handle that the galaxy's moved on, why don't you all head on down to Tosche Station to pick up some power converters?

text: What we've learned is to NOT listen to critics, and listen to the voice of the true fans....SOLO WAS AWESOME!!!! Everyone go see it in the theaters now while you can because it is the best Star Wars since Empire, or at least since Disney took over (and also Rogue One which was a very cool movie...but this one actually felt like a Star Wars and not as dark as Rogue One).  I actually heard one critic say that Last Jedi was the best Star Wars since Empire, and that's just insane to me. We all know that the first two were just a reboot of the originals for modern times. How critics won't admit that is beyond me.  They are hyping up the sequels for some reason, which helps them gross more, and bashing the spin-offs.  As for the Force Awakens and Last Jedi, they were directed, casted and filmed flawlessly, but the plot took no chances and it was just the same ol story. Did anyone even stop to ask how all a sudden the Empire is back untouched and fully restored after they were completely defeated at the end of the original saga (Return of the Jedi)?  Solo was refreshing for several reasons. First off, the story line takes the risk and doesn't just mimic the original plots. It's refreshing, creative and goes off in it's own direction. The casting was spot on for every role. Hans was perfect, Lando was awesome, and all the others as well...great on-screen chemistry. The visuals and directing were all fantastic as is no surprise for Disney and Ron Howard.  So far in my opinion, the only real successful Star Wars since Disney were Rogue One and Solo because it feels like we're watching something new and not just a modern version of the originals. Go Solo! Can't wait for the next!!
